---

<Layout title="Welcome :: AVSS2023">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-6 gap-y-12 md:grid-cols-2">
    <Card title="News" posts={posts} href="news" />
    <Card title="Program" posts={posts} href="program" />
    <Card title="Calls" posts={posts} href="calls" />
    <Card title="Submission" posts={posts} href="submission" />
    <Card title="Information" posts={posts} href="information" />
    <Card title="Attend" posts={posts} href="attend" />
    <article
      id="article"
      class="z-10 mx-auto grid w-full max-w-2xl gap-4 px-4 pb-8 font-light md:px-2"
    >
      <p>
        <b class="text-2xl font-semibold">AVSS 2023</b> is the 19th edition of the
        <b
          >IEEE International Conference on Advanced Video and Signal-Based
          Surveillance</b
        >. AVSS is the premier international conference in the field of video
        and signal-based surveillance. The goal is to provide a game-changing
        and cross-disciplinary forum that brings together experts from academia,
        industry, and government to advance the frontiers of theories, methods,
        systems, and applications.
      </p>
      <p>
        AVSS is sponsored by the
        <a target="_blank" href="https://www.computer.org/web/guest/"
          >IEEE Computer Society</a
        > (PAMI TC) and the <a
          target="_blank"
          href="https://signalprocessingsociety.org/"
          >IEEE Signal Processing Society</a
        >
        (IVMSP TC). There will be a <a
          target="_blank"
          href="https://www.cs.albany.edu/AVSS2019/program.html"
          >main conference</a
        >
        as well as multiple associated <a
          target="_blank"
          href="https://www.cs.albany.edu/AVSS2019/workshops.html">workshops</a
        >.
      </p>
    </article>
    <figure
      class="relative mx-auto min-h-[200px] w-full max-w-[450px] grayscale md:max-w-[500px]"
    >
      <img
        src="83.png"
        alt="illustration of 83 tower"
        class="absolute right-8 -bottom-36 -z-30 md:scale-100"
      />
      <img
        src="city.png"
        alt="illustration of city"
        class="absolute bottom-[-7.5rem] -left-2 -z-10 md:left-4"
      />
    </figure>
  </div>

  <style>
    /* gradient underline under the a tag using after */
    a {
      @apply relative inline-block bg-gradient-to-l from-red-500 via-rose-500 to-pink-500 bg-clip-text font-semibold text-transparent;
    }
    a::after {
      content: "";
      @apply absolute left-0 bottom-0 h-0.5 w-full origin-left scale-x-0 bg-gradient-to-l from-red-500 via-rose-500 to-pink-500 transition-transform duration-300 ease-out;
    }
    a:hover::after {
      @apply scale-x-100;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
